  "prompt": "Are maps of New York City free?",
  "response": "Yes, there are many free maps of New York City available. You can find free maps from various sources including:\n\n1. **Official Websites**: The NYC government website often provides free maps for tourists and residents.\n2. **Tourist Information Centers**: Physical copies of maps can be found at information centers around the city.\n3. **Public Libraries**: Libraries in NYC often have maps available for free.\n4. **Online Resources**: Websites like Google Maps and OpenStreetMap offer detailed maps of New York City for free.\n5. **Mobile Apps**: Many apps, including NYC-specific ones, provide free maps and navigation tools.\n\nThese resources should be adequate for navigation and exploration of New York City.",
